comment: I personally think it is a complicated situation. There are lots of people that get with people for money, or to improve their career. Their are lots of people that have been with people that have divorced and claimed lots of money, including Paul McCartney and his ex wife, also I dong know what happened but Andrew Lloyd Webber and Sarah Brightman. Personally when I saw them together I thought he still loved her thats the feeling I got, but I got the feeling she felt uncomfortable. I can't judge as I don't know what happened between them. However, if you write a role for someone, and make them the lead singer, that has to be for personal feelings. Going back to Depp, if you look at lots of his roles, some are quite crazy characters. He has played some quite creepy characters such as Sweeny Todd, sometimes people think celebrities are like the characters they play. If there are some good characters people sometimes call the celebrity their character instead of their name, which sometimes misinterprets a person. Because like with Depp, if you associate him with some of his roles, he would come across like a crazy person maybe worse, which might not be the case at all. Yet you look at someone who does lots of romantic roles, and is known for being the good looking guy that gets all the girls, people want to marry them, and wish they had someone like that, but in reality they could be crazy, but people either don't see it, or don't want to accept it. What they should think is that they are actors, these characters are only jobs, and people in jobs especially acting aren't necessarily like what they represent at work compared to chilling with friends, or family, or in relationships. Thats kind of the same in any job, because with work their is a certain role to play. As long as you are good at your job again depends on the job, but the person outside work could be anyone.
